WEBVTT

00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:09.927
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.886 --> 00:00:13.806
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:15.057 --> 00:00:16.642
At least it is true...

00:00:17.226 --> 00:00:20.896
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:39.665 --> 00:00:40.291
Guts!

00:00:40.416 --> 00:00:41.333
Take up that sword!

00:01:24.585 --> 00:01:26.712
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:26.921 --> 00:01:28.714
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:28.839 --> 00:01:32.426
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:32.718 --> 00:01:34.845
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:36.931
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:37.056 --> 00:01:39.100
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:39.350 --> 00:01:40.976
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:41.185 --> 00:01:44.605
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:48.234
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:48.984 --> 00:01:49.610
<i>I...</i>

00:01:49.985 --> 00:01:50.736
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:50.861 --> 00:01:52.863
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:53.072 --> 00:01:53.989
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:54.115 --> 00:01:54.949
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:55.074 --> 00:01:56.742
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:56.951 --> 00:01:57.868
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:58.077 --> 00:01:58.869
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:00.830
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:01.997
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:02.123 --> 00:02:02.957
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:03.124 --> 00:02:04.625
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:04.875 --> 00:02:05.960
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:06.127 --> 00:02:07.002
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:07.128 --> 00:02:07.837
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:07.962 --> 00:02:09.505
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:18.639
Moment of Glory

00:02:34.947 --> 00:02:36.323
Griffith!

00:02:42.037 --> 00:02:43.330
Wow!

00:02:43.581 --> 00:02:45.791
I didn't know that so
many people lived in Windam!

00:03:02.933 --> 00:03:04.059
Pippin!

00:03:09.607 --> 00:03:10.858
Miss Caska!

00:03:11.317 --> 00:03:13.235
My dear sister, please turn around!

00:03:13.861 --> 00:03:15.738
I can't take it...

00:03:16.197 --> 00:03:17.114
The Hawks' Raiders!

00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:19.491
Commander Guts is taking the lead!

00:03:20.451 --> 00:03:23.078
He is the man who
beat General Boscogn!

00:03:23.621 --> 00:03:25.456
He's the strongest
warrior in the Hawks!

00:03:25.706 --> 00:03:28.125
This is great!

00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:32.254
I've never seen such an
enthusiastic victory parade before.

00:03:32.755 --> 00:03:35.883
Well, why don't you wave your
arm or something, Commander?

00:03:36.091 --> 00:03:39.011
You are the hero of the battle, after all.

00:03:40.387 --> 00:03:41.013
Commander?

00:03:42.765 --> 00:03:43.974
What's the matter?

00:03:44.099 --> 00:03:46.518
You look a little down.

00:03:46.894 --> 00:03:48.479
Really, I'm okay...

00:03:49.647 --> 00:03:50.856
It's real...

00:03:52.399 --> 00:03:55.527
How could anyone even
dream of this day three years ago?

00:03:55.778 --> 00:03:57.279
That's true!

00:03:57.905 --> 00:03:59.365
But one man did...

00:03:59.865 --> 00:04:01.242
Only him...

00:04:02.618 --> 00:04:06.163
I will get my own kingdom...

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:09.375
It's amazing...

00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:10.668
...he did it...

00:04:16.048 --> 00:04:17.841
There he comes, My Lady!

00:04:18.968 --> 00:04:21.345
Look, Sir Griffith is so popular!

00:04:21.512 --> 00:04:23.639
All of the women are in a frenzy.

00:04:24.098 --> 00:04:25.891
No, don't get any closer to him!

00:04:26.016 --> 00:04:26.600
How overly familiar!

00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:28.519
Please, make haste!

00:04:28.644 --> 00:04:31.647
My Lady, please stand still, will you?

00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:33.148
Otherwise, your dress...

00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:36.026
Tell me, how do I look?

00:04:36.277 --> 00:04:37.528
You look fantastic in it.

00:04:38.112 --> 00:04:42.283
You have changed five dresses,
My Lady, you had best decide now.

00:04:42.866 --> 00:04:43.909
Really?

00:04:44.285 --> 00:04:45.536
But I think...

00:04:45.786 --> 00:04:47.871
My Lady, come here and hurry!

00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:49.915
He is passing by, hurry!

00:04:50.666 --> 00:04:51.750
Wait, wait!

00:04:53.043 --> 00:04:55.921
The Princess sure
became cheerful all of a sudden.

00:04:56.380 --> 00:05:00.926
She would barely eat when
the Hawks were in the field.

00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:09.310
Sir Griffith!

00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:15.566
Oh, no!

00:05:16.025 --> 00:05:18.527
It is impossible in this noisy crowd.

00:05:18.819 --> 00:05:20.696
You had best wait until the celebration.

00:05:29.705 --> 00:05:31.165
Did you make the arrangements?

00:05:31.582 --> 00:05:33.042
Consider it done.

00:05:34.043 --> 00:05:39.340
We should hold a feast to celebrate
after everything has fallen into place.

00:05:39.923 --> 00:05:42.468
A feast held to express
our regrets over his death.

00:05:42.926 --> 00:05:44.595
This is ironic.

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:49.350
The White Hawk of the battlefield will
meet his end caged within these stone walls.

00:05:50.476 --> 00:05:54.563
Of course, it will happen on this
day, the most notable in his entire life.

00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:57.191
This is merciful, at least.

00:05:57.358 --> 00:05:58.108
Minister Foss!

00:06:01.362 --> 00:06:02.112
What's happened?

00:06:02.363 --> 00:06:03.864
I brought a letter addressed to you, sir.

00:06:04.990 --> 00:06:05.866
A letter?

00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:07.451
But from who?

00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:08.869
I do not know.

00:06:09.078 --> 00:06:10.996
A lady from the court
entrusted this to me.

00:06:11.121 --> 00:06:11.747
Excuse me.

00:06:18.754 --> 00:06:20.381
T-This is...

00:06:20.881 --> 00:06:22.508
What is the matter, Minister Foss?

00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:25.469
W-Well...

00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:28.389
Nothing is the matter, Your Majesty.

00:06:30.224 --> 00:06:36.397
I have a little errand to take
care of, so please excuse me.

00:06:36.522 --> 00:06:38.023
See you later, then.

00:06:47.241 --> 00:06:48.158
How?

00:06:49.493 --> 00:06:51.412
How did this happen?

00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:54.289
Bastard!

00:07:26.405 --> 00:07:27.197
Look!

00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:29.700
Here comes Sir Griffith!

00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:31.702
The members of the Hawks?

00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:33.412
They are the
guardian angels of Midland!

00:07:45.215 --> 00:07:46.091
I bet...

00:07:46.592 --> 00:07:49.970
...the money commoners work hard for
is taxed away and spent on this place.

00:07:50.095 --> 00:07:50.721
Yeah...

00:07:53.056 --> 00:07:55.058
Hey, stick out your chest!

00:07:55.225 --> 00:07:57.352
They will look down on
you if you aren't confident!

00:07:57.478 --> 00:08:00.230
I'm so nervous, it's embarrassing.

00:08:00.481 --> 00:08:04.860
But, we have come this far at last.

00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:06.695
That's true.

00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:11.366
I can't believe that I'm standing in a
place I've only heard about in faerie tales!

00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:16.830
If I didn't meet the Hawks and Griffith...

00:08:17.206 --> 00:08:21.752
...I would never have even
imagined this sight, not even in a dream...

00:08:22.002 --> 00:08:24.880
Me, surrounded by
nobles in a huge castle like this.

00:08:30.886 --> 00:08:32.012
Sir Griffith!

00:08:33.388 --> 00:08:34.556
Welcome back, My Lord.

00:08:34.681 --> 00:08:37.184
Pleased to see you safe,
we were worried about you.

00:08:38.560 --> 00:08:41.647
I heard the Hawks carried the
battle on their shoulders again.

00:08:41.772 --> 00:08:44.191
Please tell us your
stories of the battlefield.

00:08:44.816 --> 00:08:47.027
Would you mind if I
offered myself for a dance later?

00:08:47.319 --> 00:08:49.530
I would love to dance with you, too!

00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:50.447
No, tell us your story first.

00:08:50.781 --> 00:08:56.578
I am afraid of boring you ladies
by telling a barbarous war tale.

00:08:56.662 --> 00:09:00.582
We will never be bored
at all, it's very exciting!

00:09:00.832 --> 00:09:01.708
Yes!

00:09:02.709 --> 00:09:04.086
Wow...

00:09:04.294 --> 00:09:05.837
He certainly seems at home...

00:09:05.963 --> 00:09:10.551
Damn, he should
share one of them with me!

00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:12.844
You must be the
commanders of the Hawks?

00:09:13.303 --> 00:09:15.722
I would like you to tell me of your
heroic exploits on the battlefield.

00:09:15.847 --> 00:09:18.809
You certainly are strong, aren't you?

00:09:19.434 --> 00:09:22.354
Well, I really am, I must confess.

00:09:22.604 --> 00:09:24.940
I am even afraid of my own strength.

00:09:25.607 --> 00:09:27.109
It's you, isn't it?

00:09:27.442 --> 00:09:28.694
The Commander of
the Hawk's Raiders...

00:09:28.819 --> 00:09:31.488
...the one who defeated
General Boscogn in single combat?

00:09:32.239 --> 00:09:33.740
Y-Yeah...

00:09:33.865 --> 00:09:35.200
How fabulous!

00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:36.493
Despite the fact
that General Boscogn...

00:09:36.702 --> 00:09:40.247
...was their big hero and his reputation
is still widely known in every country.

00:09:40.372 --> 00:09:40.956
That's true!

00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:42.374
I also heard...

00:09:42.499 --> 00:09:45.586
...that you fought against a hundred
men and defeated them all by yourself.

00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:46.962
Is that true?

00:09:47.254 --> 00:09:49.006
Y-Yeah...

00:09:49.131 --> 00:09:50.757
This is unbelievable!

00:09:50.966 --> 00:09:53.719
Are you the
strongest man in the Hawks?

00:09:53.844 --> 00:09:56.513
Who is stronger, Sir Griffith or you?

00:09:59.266 --> 00:10:00.726
Hey, you take care of them!

00:10:00.851 --> 00:10:01.768
Oh, no!

00:10:01.893 --> 00:10:03.228
He's leaving!

00:10:03.270 --> 00:10:05.022
All right, no problem!

00:10:05.397 --> 00:10:07.149
It's not fair, Guts!

00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:09.359
So cute!

00:10:09.735 --> 00:10:10.485
Um...

00:10:10.736 --> 00:10:12.029
How muscular!

00:10:12.237 --> 00:10:14.031
Let me touch, let me touch!

00:10:21.163 --> 00:10:22.664
They are all swollen-headed...

00:10:23.165 --> 00:10:26.293
Deep down, all of them
probably feel undeserving of this praise.

00:10:26.418 --> 00:10:28.170
Perhaps...

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:34.301
But, even the generals cannot help
admitting the Hawks' real capability.

00:10:34.676 --> 00:10:36.011
Sure they cannot...

00:10:36.428 --> 00:10:38.555
...because the Hawks fulfilled
our the long cherished wish...

00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:41.308
...of our kingdom,
after one hundred years.

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:43.560
As if it were nothing.

00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:47.189
It was rewarding for you to
speak up for him before, Sir Raban.

00:10:47.648 --> 00:10:49.900
You have foresight and
I will follow your example.

00:10:50.317 --> 00:10:54.071
You are talking like some
scheming minister, Sir Owen.

00:10:54.946 --> 00:10:59.451
However, we will all need
to be a little like that in future.

00:11:00.202 --> 00:11:01.662
The war is over.

00:11:02.079 --> 00:11:07.709
I pray to God that the upcoming
peace and tranquility will last for ages...

00:11:08.543 --> 00:11:14.216
In a period of peace, warriors like us
who only know how to wield swords...

00:11:14.466 --> 00:11:17.928
...have to find a new way
to survive within the castle.

00:11:18.679 --> 00:11:24.309
Ironically, the man who brought
this peace must also be aware of this...

00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:29.856
That man stands out
so much, it will be difficult...

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:32.484
...for him to survive within the
castle during a time of peace.

00:11:33.235 --> 00:11:35.696
The stronger that any light shines...

00:11:36.488 --> 00:11:38.740
...the darker the nearby shadows grow.

00:11:49.376 --> 00:11:50.335
Oh, geez...

00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:52.254
I can't deal with this.

00:11:52.754 --> 00:11:53.880
What are they doing?

00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:08.395
Come on!

00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:09.646
H-Hey, wait...

00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:10.272
What the...

00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:11.648
Who the hell are you?

00:12:13.775 --> 00:12:16.153
Those men are pestering me,
and I don't know what to do.

00:12:16.528 --> 00:12:18.739
I want you to pretend
you're my partner for a while.

00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:21.867
It's annoying!

00:12:21.992 --> 00:12:25.912
I guess those useless sons of
noblemen don't see many female warriors.

00:12:26.163 --> 00:12:28.415
They look at me like I'm
some kind of rare animal...

00:12:33.128 --> 00:12:34.546
What are you looking at?

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:36.548
I didn't know you liked to wear...

00:12:39.676 --> 00:12:41.178
Don't tell me that...

00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:44.431
Just come this way!

00:12:46.016 --> 00:12:47.058
How embarrassing!

00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:49.060
It's not my fault!

00:12:54.191 --> 00:12:55.901
I see...

00:12:58.278 --> 00:13:00.655
I'm not very good
at these kind of things.

00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:04.326
Wielding a sword is
much more comfortable.

00:13:04.701 --> 00:13:05.660
I agree.

00:13:06.453 --> 00:13:08.205
But I wonder what put
such an idea into your head?

00:13:08.413 --> 00:13:12.584
To think that you, our brave sister
Caska, is wearing a flowing dress...

00:13:12.834 --> 00:13:15.962
I usually dress like a man just
because it's easier to move that way.

00:13:16.087 --> 00:13:18.590
It doesn't mean that I'm
fond of wearing men's clothes!

00:13:20.967 --> 00:13:21.843
But...

00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:25.180
I shouldn't have done
something I'm not used to.

00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:29.226
I'll make myself sick if I keep
wearing this kind of loose dress.

00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:34.564
To come to think it,
I haven't worn a skirt for so long...

00:13:34.981 --> 00:13:36.733
And look at all my muscle...

00:13:37.609 --> 00:13:39.694
Don't I look ridiculous?

00:13:39.945 --> 00:13:41.988
No, you look good.

00:13:42.197 --> 00:13:43.198
Really?

00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:49.621
Sure, you look better than the
noble girls crowding around Griffith.

00:13:53.834 --> 00:13:57.629
Hey, why don't you ask
Griffith to dance with you?

00:13:58.380 --> 00:13:59.256
No...

00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:01.383
It's impossible...

00:14:02.217 --> 00:14:05.971
I haven't danced since the small
festivals in my village when I was a kid...

00:14:06.471 --> 00:14:08.890
I'd end up stepping on Griffith's feet...

00:14:12.978 --> 00:14:16.273
Anyway, tell me why you've
had such a change of heart.

00:14:16.648 --> 00:14:20.902
You've never showed up in
conservative places like this before...

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.492
I want to see
everything through to the end...

00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:28.118
What?

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:31.371
Ever since I met you three years ago...

00:14:31.872 --> 00:14:33.290
...what Griffith and I...

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:35.876
...what everyone has
done within these years...

00:14:36.877 --> 00:14:44.301
...and what he has won so far,
and what he will win in the future...

00:14:45.302 --> 00:14:47.012
I want to see it to the end.

00:14:47.304 --> 00:14:48.430
That's why I came.

00:14:54.686 --> 00:14:55.687
Guts...

00:14:57.063 --> 00:14:58.440
...you want to leave...

00:14:59.316 --> 00:15:00.442
...the Band of the Hawk.

00:15:03.194 --> 00:15:04.446
For real?

00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:10.327
No matter what?

00:15:16.917 --> 00:15:18.293
Long live the King!

00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:19.586
Long live the King!

00:15:25.842 --> 00:15:27.677
There's our sponsor now.

00:15:30.805 --> 00:15:32.474
You go on ahead.

00:15:32.724 --> 00:15:34.601
I'll stay here and cool off for a while.

00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:38.980
I can't stand listening to
the King's tedious speeches.

00:15:39.189 --> 00:15:40.190
Don't be too long.

00:15:40.357 --> 00:15:40.857
Sure...

00:15:43.234 --> 00:15:44.110
You...

00:15:44.611 --> 00:15:45.195
What?

00:15:46.613 --> 00:15:47.364
No...

00:15:48.615 --> 00:15:49.741
Nothing...

00:16:00.710 --> 00:16:04.756
There is another reason why
I'm here at this evening party.

00:16:06.383 --> 00:16:09.010
No one knows what will
happen here in a few moments.

00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:12.263
Neither Caska nor the
other members of the Hawks...

00:16:14.224 --> 00:16:17.477
It's a little too much
for them, isn't it, Griffith?

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:23.900
First of all, I shall share
some good news with you.

00:16:25.235 --> 00:16:30.240
A little while ago, the Chuder special
envoy sent representatives to our kingdom.

00:16:30.407 --> 00:16:33.785
They carried a signed armistice treaty.

00:16:34.244 --> 00:16:39.499
I am most grateful for the toil and
ordeals you have endured for so long.

00:16:39.541 --> 00:16:42.293
I should like to
express my utmost gratitude.

00:16:43.253 --> 00:16:48.174
It is understandable that more
than few of you might be displeased...

00:16:48.633 --> 00:16:49.759
...by the armistice.

00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:52.804
After all, many of you lost
your family and friends to this war...

00:16:53.054 --> 00:16:57.934
...and our enmity toward Chuder
has been harbored for generations.

00:16:58.435 --> 00:17:03.189
However, it is urgent for
us to rebuild our kingdom.

00:17:03.314 --> 00:17:06.776
Our kingdom has been
exhausted due to the war effort.

00:17:07.110 --> 00:17:12.782
I expect you all to use your capabilities
to contribute prosperity to my reign.

00:17:14.659 --> 00:17:16.536
As you well know...

00:17:17.245 --> 00:17:23.001
...this armistice is made possible by the
Band of the Hawk, led by Count Griffith.

00:17:23.126 --> 00:17:25.170
It is due to their distinguished services.

00:17:25.628 --> 00:17:27.130
During the past one hundred years...

00:17:27.255 --> 00:17:30.675
...it has been said the conquering
of Doldrey would be utterly impossible.

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:37.182
But they succeeded in such an
undertaking with unparalleled courage.

00:17:37.432 --> 00:17:39.809
Excuse me, let me pass please.

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:45.523
And I will inform you now, at this
joyous celebration, that there will be...

00:17:45.815 --> 00:17:49.027
...a rite of decoration held
on the day after tomorrow...

00:17:49.152 --> 00:17:54.324
I believe it might be proper for me
to grant Count Griffith and the Hawks...

00:17:54.449 --> 00:18:00.038
...the title of White Knights, the title of
supreme command over Midland's armies...

00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:03.208
The titles most
appropriate to be granted...

00:18:03.333 --> 00:18:07.462
...are the White Hawk General
Griffith, and the White Hawk Knights.

00:18:07.921 --> 00:18:11.091
All of the commanders
of the Hawk's companies...

00:18:11.466 --> 00:18:16.971
...will be personally knighted
by me and raised to the peerage.

00:18:17.597 --> 00:18:18.973
The White Hawk General!

00:18:19.224 --> 00:18:20.975
The White Hawk Knights!

00:18:21.351 --> 00:18:22.227
Wonderful!

00:18:22.352 --> 00:18:23.353
It's fantastic!

00:18:31.486 --> 00:18:33.571
I can't believe this...

00:18:33.947 --> 00:18:36.116
...we will become nobles?

00:18:55.593 --> 00:18:57.262
Isn't it wonderful?

00:18:57.512 --> 00:18:58.888
Uh, thank you...

00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:01.850
Please let me pass.

00:19:07.397 --> 00:19:08.523
Why...

00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:11.609
...the man who rose from commoners
is promoted to the highest rank in Midland.

00:19:11.860 --> 00:19:13.111
Utter nonsense...

00:19:13.611 --> 00:19:15.530
This is quite unexpected.

00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:16.406
Indeed...

00:19:17.532 --> 00:19:18.908
This is great!

00:19:20.410 --> 00:19:23.037
You will meet your end shortly...

00:19:23.121 --> 00:19:26.499
Become drunk on your illusive
prosperity while you still can.

00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:35.258
It is about time, Mr. Foss.

00:19:37.177 --> 00:19:38.553
What's wrong with you?

00:19:38.678 --> 00:19:40.680
You really look pale...

00:19:42.432 --> 00:19:43.933
This is unlike you.

00:19:44.058 --> 00:19:46.060
Is it because you are afraid of...

00:19:46.186 --> 00:19:48.813
N-No, of course I'm not...

00:19:49.147 --> 00:19:51.441
Please pull yourself together, Mr. Foss.

00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:22.972
Please, sir.

00:20:24.349 --> 00:20:26.100
Certainly, thank you.

00:20:38.947 --> 00:20:43.868
Now, we should toast the
celebration of our young heroes...

00:20:44.244 --> 00:20:48.498
...and of course, the
future prosperity of Midland.

00:20:48.873 --> 00:20:50.959
Excuse me, let me pass please.

00:20:51.376 --> 00:20:52.460
Raise your glass!

00:20:53.253 --> 00:20:55.129
Raise your glass!

00:20:55.713 --> 00:20:56.756
Cheers!

00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:00.760
Please, make way.

00:21:06.599 --> 00:21:07.475
Griffith...

00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:42.427
Griffith!

00:22:02.947 --> 00:22:05.074
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.786
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.790
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:19.047
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.172 --> 00:22:20.298
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.423 --> 00:22:23.468
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.722 --> 00:22:30.975
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.309 --> 00:22:34.604
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:35.063 --> 00:22:37.982
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:41.694
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:45.365
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:08.971 --> 00:23:13.976
What does a man think when he
reaches the summit of his dream?

00:23:14.519 --> 00:23:20.400
Days long past, future
ambitions, or the emotion of love?

00:23:21.025 --> 00:23:24.654
Dreams are to be fulfilled
for a man's own self, but...

00:23:25.530 --> 00:23:27.740
...in his pursuit,
he loses something else.

00:23:28.282 --> 00:23:31.494
By the time he realizes it is gone,
will it be too late to restore what is lost?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Tombstone of Flames

